Nail biting has been a lifelong issue for me. I do it when nervous but also when bored and on 'auto-pilot.' I've tried the nailpolish that gives a bad taste in your mouth but then it gives that taste to any food you touch with your hands. Have tried keeping nails polished and pretty (but I need to have a good time period before they get that way first...) and have tried telling those around me to let me know when I'm doing it.
Well, I have really never had a problem with this behavior in the past, so it is just recent but I would say that I would have to depend on willpower and distractions.
